import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time

# Load cryptocurrency data
crypto_file_path = 'C://Users//56249//Desktop//datasets//coin_Bitcoin.csv' 
crypto_data = pd.read_csv(crypto_file_path)

# Convert Date column to datetime and set it as index
crypto_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(crypto_data['Date'])
crypto_data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

# Fill missing values using the average of the previous and next values
crypto_data['Close'] = crypto_data['Close'].interpolate(method='linear')

# Visualize the cleaned data
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(crypto_data['Close'])
plt.title('Cryptocurrency Close Prices')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Close Price')
plt.show()

#Calculate EMA and RSI for Cryptocurrency Data
In [3]:
# For Linear Regression Model (EMA=12, RSI=14)
crypto_data['EMA12_LR'] = crypto_data['Close'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()

delta = crypto_data['Close'].diff(1)
gain = delta.where(delta > 0, 0)
loss = -delta.where(delta < 0, 0)
avg_gain = gain.rolling(window=14).mean()
avg_loss = loss.rolling(window=14).mean()
rs = avg_gain / avg_loss
crypto_data['RSI14_LR'] = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))

# For Random Forest Model (EMA=200, RSI=200)
crypto_data['EMA200_RF'] = crypto_data['Close'].ewm(span=200, adjust=False).mean()

delta = crypto_data['Close'].diff(1)
gain = delta.where(delta > 0, 0)
loss = -delta.where(delta < 0, 0)
avg_gain = gain.rolling(window=200).mean()
avg_loss = loss.rolling(window=200).mean()
rs = avg_gain / avg_loss
crypto_data['RSI200_RF'] = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))

# Drop rows with NaN values resulting from rolling calculations
crypto_data = crypto_data.dropna()

# Display the cleaned and feature-engineered data
print(crypto_data.head())

# Load stock market data
stock_file_path = 'C://Users//56249//Desktop//datasets//all_stocks_5yr.csv' 
stock_data = pd.read_csv(stock_file_path)

# Select AAPL data
apple_data = stock_data[stock_data['Name'] == 'AAPL'].copy()

# Convert date column to datetime and set it as index
apple_data.loc[:, 'date'] = pd.to_datetime(apple_data['date'])
apple_data.set_index('date', inplace=True)

# Fill missing values using the average of the previous and next values
apple_data.loc[:, 'close'] = apple_data['close'].interpolate(method='linear')

# Visualize the cleaned data
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(apple_data['close'])
plt.title('AAPL Close Prices')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Close Price')
plt.show()

# For both models (EMA=12, RSI=50)
apple_data['EMA12'] = apple_data['close'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()

delta = apple_data['close'].diff(1)
gain = delta.where(delta > 0, 0)
loss = -delta.where(delta < 0, 0)
avg_gain = gain.rolling(window=50).mean()
avg_loss = loss.rolling(window=50).mean()
rs = avg_gain / avg_loss
apple_data['RSI50'] = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))

# Drop rows with NaN values resulting from rolling calculations
apple_data = apple_data.dropna()

#Cryptocurrency Data
# Feature selection for Linear Regression (EMA=12, RSI=14)
crypto_features_lr = crypto_data[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Volume', 'EMA12_LR', 'RSI14_LR']]
crypto_target = crypto_data['Close']

# Feature selection for Random Forest (EMA=200, RSI=200)
crypto_features_rf = crypto_data[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Volume', 'EMA200_RF', 'RSI200_RF']]

# Split data into training and testing sets
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
X_crypto_train_lr, X_crypto_test_lr, y_crypto_train, y_crypto_test = train_test_split(crypto_features_lr, crypto_target, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
X_crypto_train_rf, X_crypto_test_rf, _, _ = train_test_split(crypto_features_rf, crypto_target, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Standardize data
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
crypto_scaler_lr = StandardScaler()
X_crypto_train_scaled_lr = crypto_scaler_lr.fit_transform(X_crypto_train_lr)
X_crypto_test_scaled_lr = crypto_scaler_lr.transform(X_crypto_test_lr)

crypto_scaler_rf = StandardScaler()
X_crypto_train_scaled_rf = crypto_scaler_rf.fit_transform(X_crypto_train_rf)
X_crypto_test_scaled_rf = crypto_scaler_rf.transform(X_crypto_test_rf)

#Linear Regression Model

from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_percentage_error
import time

# Train and evaluate on cryptocurrency data (EMA=12, RSI=14)
start_time = time.time()
lr_crypto_model = LinearRegression()
lr_crypto_model.fit(X_crypto_train_scaled_lr, y_crypto_train)
y_crypto_pred_lr = lr_crypto_model.predict(X_crypto_test_scaled_lr)
crypto_lr_time = time.time() - start_time

rmse_crypto_lr = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_crypto_test, y_crypto_pred_lr))
mape_crypto_lr = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_crypto_test, y_crypto_pred_lr)

# Train and evaluate on stock market data (EMA=12, RSI=50)
start_time = time.time()
lr_stock_model = LinearRegression()
lr_stock_model.fit(X_stock_train_scaled, y_stock_train)
y_stock_pred_lr = lr_stock_model.predict(X_stock_test_scaled)
stock_lr_time = time.time() - start_time

rmse_stock_lr = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_stock_test, y_stock_pred_lr))
mape_stock_lr = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_stock_test, y_stock_pred_lr)

print(f'Linear Regression - Cryptocurrency Market RMSE: {rmse_crypto_lr}, MAPE: {mape_crypto_lr}, Time: {crypto_lr_time}')
print(f'Linear Regression - Stock Market RMSE: {rmse_stock_lr}, MAPE: {mape_stock_lr}, Time: {stock_lr_time}')

Linear Regression - Cryptocurrency Market RMSE: 244.31569026517423, MAPE: 0.02324730386026121, Time: 0.08312082290649414
Linear Regression - Stock Market RMSE: 0.5251903258407615, MAPE: 0.003721814175785151, Time: 0.0020041465759277344

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor

# Train and evaluate on cryptocurrency data (EMA=200, RSI=200)
start_time = time.time()
rf_crypto_model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
rf_crypto_model.fit(X_crypto_train_scaled_rf, y_crypto_train)
y_crypto_pred_rf = rf_crypto_model.predict(X_crypto_test_scaled_rf)
crypto_rf_time = time.time() - start_time

rmse_crypto_rf = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_crypto_test, y_crypto_pred_rf))
mape_crypto_rf = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_crypto_test, y_crypto_pred_rf)

# Train and evaluate on stock market data (EMA=12, RSI=50)
start_time = time.time()
rf_stock_model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
rf_stock_model.fit(X_stock_train_scaled, y_stock_train)
y_stock_pred_rf = rf_stock_model.predict(X_stock_test_scaled)
stock_rf_time = time.time() - start_time

rmse_stock_rf = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_stock_test, y_stock_pred_rf))
mape_stock_rf = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_stock_test, y_stock_pred_rf)

print(f'Random Forest - Cryptocurrency Market RMSE: {rmse_crypto_rf}, MAPE: {mape_crypto_rf}, Time: {crypto_rf_time}')
print(f'Random Forest - Stock Market RMSE: {rmse_stock_rf}, MAPE: {mape_stock_rf}, Time: {stock_rf_time}')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

rmse_crypto_lr = 244.31569026517423
mape_crypto_lr = 0.02324730386026121
crypto_lr_time = 0.006997346878051758

rmse_stock_lr = 0.5251903258407615
mape_stock_lr = 0.003721814175785151
stock_lr_time = 0.0019965171813964844

rmse_crypto_rf = 358.05896108770827
mape_crypto_rf = 0.013474328658482158
crypto_rf_time = 1.3801145553588867

rmse_stock_rf = 0.7488510456140073
mape_stock_rf = 0.0051884902519652295
stock_rf_time = 0.5253300666809082

labels = ['LR - Crypto', 'LR - Stock', 'RF - Crypto', 'RF - Stock']
rmse_values = [rmse_crypto_lr, rmse_stock_lr, rmse_crypto_rf, rmse_stock_rf]
mape_values = [mape_crypto_lr, mape_stock_lr, mape_crypto_rf, mape_stock_rf]
time_values = [crypto_lr_time, stock_lr_time, crypto_rf_time, stock_rf_time]

x = np.arange(len(labels)) 
width = 0.35  

fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))

ax1.bar(x, rmse_values, width, label='RMSE', color=['blue', 'blue', 'green', 'green'])
ax1.set_xlabel('Models')
ax1.set_ylabel('RMSE')
ax1.set_title('RMSE Comparison')
ax1.set_xticks(x)
ax1.set_xticklabels(labels)

ax2.bar(x, mape_values, width, label='MAPE', color=['blue', 'blue', 'green', 'green'])
ax2.set_xlabel('Models')
ax2.set_ylabel('MAPE')
ax2.set_title('MAPE Comparison')
ax2.set_xticks(x)
ax2.set_xticklabels(labels)

ax3.bar(x, time_values, width, label='Time', color=['blue', 'blue', 'green', 'green'])
ax3.set_xlabel('Models')
ax3.set_ylabel('Time (s)')
ax3.set_title('Time Comparison')
ax3.set_xticks(x)
ax3.set_xticklabels(labels)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
